First of all, thank you for choosing to use or try out my launcher.

The reason I developed this launcher goes back to a day when, after a long break, I wanted to play Minecraft. However, I kept running into so many damn problems. Eventually, I got fed up and thought to myself, "What if I just make my own launcher?" I started researching, did some things in the terminal, and when I realized Minecraft actually launched, I was completely stunned. After that, I added an interface, kept improving it, and thought, "Why not release this to everyone?" because I’m sure many of you are facing those same damn problems too.

There might still be some issues within the launcher. Whenever an idea pops into my mind, I try to implement and develop it. You will most likely encounter some bugs, but I managed to fix most of them before releasing this version. You will probably only run into minor issues, so please don't hesitate to report them to me—just please don't be rude about it. This is one of my very first attempts, and to be honest, I wouldn't consider myself a coding expert yet.

Thank you again for your support.

